s Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at thirty-one), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993). The Hooker-Zastrow line traces forward through Ethel; the Hebner-Cook-Stafford family that descended from these children is doubly Hooker-descended on both maternal and paternal sides."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born Murray NY 1865, died Holley 1915","body":"Lydia Mason Robinson was born July 9 or 10, 1865 in Murray, Orleans County New York. She died February 8, 1915 in Holley, Orleans County New York at age forty-nine — predeceasing her husband William Henry by eighteen years. The Orleans County NY core of the Hooker-Shader-Robinson cousin network spanned three generations of intermarriages within the same upstate New York county."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"lydia-hooker-1865"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"HD3270","slug":"lydia-hooker-1865","n":"Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker","by":1865,"dy":1915,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":10},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"H03880","slug":"william-hooker-1864","n":"William Henry Hooker","by":1864,"dy":1933,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":9},"year":1889,"children":[{"id":"HD3236","slug":"c-hooker-1891","n":"C Theodore Hooker","by":1891,"dy":1971,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":10},{"id":"HD3237","slug":"ethel-zastrow-1896","n":"Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow","by":1896,"dy":1928,"sx":"f","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":10},{"id":"HD3238","slug":"marjory-delahanty-1902","n":"Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty","by":1902,"dy":1993,"sx":"f","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":10}]}],"parents":{"father":{"id":"X02287","slug":"john-robinson-1831","n":"John William Robinson","by":1831,"dy":1924,"sx":"u","hd":false,"td":false,"ee":false,"g